title: Grateful Dead Live at Oakland-Alameda County Stadium on 1987-07-24
description:
Set 1

Jack Straw, Mississippi Half Step, My Brother Esau, Friend Of The Devil, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, When Push Comes To Shove, Far From Me, Cassidy, Deal

Set 2

Hell In A Bucket, Scarlet Begonias, Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> Uncle John's Band-> Dear Mr. Fantasy-> I Need A Miracle-> Bertha-> Sugar Magnolia

Set 3

Cryptical Envelopement, Man Of Peace, Maggie's Farm, I'll Be Your Baby Tonight, I Want You, Highway 61 Revisited, It's All Over Now Baby Blue, Memphis Blues, Ballad Of A Thin Man, Shelter From The Storm, Slow Train Coming, Knockin' On Heaven's Door, E:Touch Of Gray-> E: All Along The Watchtower

Third set with Bob Dylan

throw me in the jailhouse After getting out of jail in utah for something green on my way to Autzen, I spanked the grey dog from SLC to Oakland and even got a $5 ticket.
I enjoy the AKG sound on this and the crowd wasn't horrible... nice for a stadium AUD
